The paper deals with network utility maximization problems in heterogeneous cellular networks, which are typically studied in the computer networks and communications (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also considers coordination among serving nodes, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the weighted sum rate system utility and proportional fairness, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
